{"lemma":"رُكْنَيْ","slug":"رُكْنَيْ","root":"ر.ك.ن","root_slug":"ر-ك-ن","root_link":"/words/roots/ر-ك-ن","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"رُكْن","root":"ركن","pos":"N","occurrence_count":2},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":9},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n16544","n16547","n16548"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B1%D9%8F%D9%83%D9%92%D9%86%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"the intersection of two surfaces or edges, a corner","tags":["countable"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"the intersection of two surfaces or edges, a corner; a faraway, remote, or secluded place; a nook","tags":["countable"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"an object that joins two surfaces at a point, a cornerstone","tags":["countable"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"an object that joins two surfaces at a point, a cornerstone; a fundamental idea, doctrine, or act","tags":["countable"],"examples":[{"text":"أَرْكَانُ الْإِسْلَامِ الْخَمْسَة","english":"The Five Cornerstones of Islam."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to incline to, to lean upon","tags":["countable","obsolete"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to rely upon, to trust, to lean upon","tags":["countable","figuratively"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to seek comfort in, to be lulled by, to keep to","tags":["countable","figuratively"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to park","tags":["countable"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be dignified and respectful","tags":["countable"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/rukn/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n16544","headword_ar":"ركّن","root":"rkn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"is said by Golius, as on the authority of the KL, to signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made like,"},{"kind":"text","text":"“ similem fecit: ” and hence Freytag also thus explains it: but it is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zk~n","text_ar":"زكّن"},{"kind":"text","text":"that has this signification. In my copy of the KL,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tazokiynN","text_ar":"تَزْكِينٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(not"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tarokiynN","text_ar":"تَرْكِينٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":") is expl. by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mAnnd krdn","text_ar":"مانند كردن"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n16547","headword_ar":"رَكْنٌ","root":"rkn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jura*","text_ar":"جُرَذ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"large field-rat"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faA^or","text_ar":"فَاْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"common rat"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mouse"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rukayonN","text_ar":"رُكَيْنٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n16548","headword_ar":"رُكْنٌ","root":"rkn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAnib","text_ar":"جَانِب"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"side,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"outward part,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] of a thing: (Msb:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strongest"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAnib","text_ar":"جَانِب"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1149},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"side,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"outward part,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (S, K, TA) of a thing (S, TA) of any kind: (TA:) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"corner,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"angle,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zaAwiyap","text_ar":"زَاوِيَة"},{"kind":"text","text":",) of a house or room or the like: (K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zwY","text_ar":"زوى"},{"kind":"text","text":":) [and this is perhaps what is meant by the “ strongest"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jAnb","text_ar":"جانب"},{"kind":"text","text":"; ” for the strongest outward part of the house is unquestionably the corner, or angle: thus the angle in which is the Black Stone, of the Kaabeh, is specially called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rukonu","text_ar":"رُكْنُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Albayoti","text_ar":"البَيْتِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rukonu bayoti A@ll~`hi","text_ar":"رُكْنُ بَيْتِ ا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rukon","text_ar":"رُكْن"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaSor","text_ar":"قَصْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or palace, or pavilion, &c.,] is its"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAnib","text_ar":"جَانِب"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or its strongest"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jAnb","text_ar":"جانب"},{"kind":"text","text":"], and so of a mountain: (TA: [see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakuna","text_ar":"رَكُنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakiynN","text_ar":"رَكِينٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":]) the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arokaAnN","text_ar":"اَرْكَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arokunN","text_ar":"اَرْكُنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[each properly a pl. of pauc., but the former is used as a pl. of mult.]: (Msb, TA:) the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arokaAn","text_ar":"اَرْكَان"},{"kind":"text","text":"of anything are is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jawaAnib","text_ar":"جَوَانِب"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sides,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"outward parts,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or its"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"corners,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"angles,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon which it rests, and by which it is supported:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arokaAn","text_ar":"اَرْكَان"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a land are its"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extremities"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sides"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"corners"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Ham p. 478.) ―         -b2-  [Hence, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A stay,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"support,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of any kind: see an ex. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mirojamN","text_ar":"مِرْجَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": whence, perhaps,] one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tamas~aHotu biA^arokaAnihi","text_ar":"تَمَسَّحْتُ بِاَرْكَانِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tabar~akotu bihi","text_ar":"تَبَرَّكْتُ بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  [i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I looked for a blessing by means of him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A thing whereby one is strengthened"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA yuqaw~aY bihi","text_ar":"مَا يُقَوَّى بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mA","text_ar":"ما"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taqaw~aYbh","text_ar":"تَقَوَّىبه"},{"kind":"text","text":"]),"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as dominion"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mulok","text_ar":"مُلْك"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"malik","text_ar":"مَلِك"},{"kind":"text","text":"]),"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and an army,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a military force,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: (K:) and thus it has been explained as occurring in the Kur [li. 39], where it is said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fatawal~aY birukonihi","text_ar":"فَتَوَلَّى بِرُكْنِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) i. e. (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And he turned away from belief with his forces;"},{"kind":"text","text":"because they were to him like the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rukon","text_ar":"رُكْن"},{"kind":"text","text":"[properly so termed]. (Jel.) (assumed tropical:)  A man's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"kinsfolk;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nearer,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nearest, relations;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"clan;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tribe;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea$iyrapN","text_ar":"عَشِيرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (AHeyth, TA:) (assumed tropical:)  a man's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"people,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"party;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"higher among them;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"persons by whom he is aided and strengthened:"},{"kind":"text","text":"thought by ISd to be thus called by way of comparison [to a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rukon","text_ar":"رُكْن"},{"kind":"text","text":"properly so termed]: and thus it has been explained as used in the Kur [xi. 82], where it is said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awo A=wiYa rukonK $adiydK","text_ar":"اَوْ ا=وِىَ رُكْنٍ شَدِيدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Or that I might have recourse to a strong people,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"party,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]: (TA:) or it here means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea$iyrap","text_ar":"عَشِيرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[explained above]. (Jel.) And (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A noble,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"high, person;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa rukonN mino","text_ar":"هُوَ رُكْنٌ مِنْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arokaAni qawomihi","text_ar":"اَرْكَانِ قَوْمِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is a noble, of the nobles of his people"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arokaAnu AlA_inosaAni","text_ar":"اَرْكَانُ الاـِنْسَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The members,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"limbs, of the man, with which things are gained"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"earned,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with which he works;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as the hands or arms, and the feet or legs. (TA.) ―         -b3-  Also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Might,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"resistance:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) so in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa yaA^owiY A_ilaY rukonK $adiydK","text_ar":"هُوَ يَاْوِى اـِلَى رُكْنٍ شَدِيدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He has recourse to strong,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vehement, might"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"resistance"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S:) and so it has been explained as used in the words of the Kur last cited above. (TA.) ―         -b4-  And (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A thing, an affair, a case, an event,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an action, of great magnitude"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"moment, momentous, formidable,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"terrible."},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHeyth, K.) Thus AHeyth explains it as used in the saying of En-Nábighah [Edh-Dhubyánee],"},{"kind":"quote","text":"laA taqo*ifan~iY birukonK laA kifaA='a lahu"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"By no means reproach thou me with a momentous,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a formidable, thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"action,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an enormity, that has not its equal;"},{"kind":"text","text":"though (he proceeds to say) the enemies incite thee, with companies of men aiding one another]. (TA.) ―         -b5-  In the conventional language [of the schools],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rukonu Al$~aYo'i","text_ar":"رُكْنُ الشَّىْءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means (assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The essence of the thing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that whereby the thing subsists:"},{"kind":"text","text":"from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~aqaw~umu","text_ar":"التَّقَوُّمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; because the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qiwaAm","text_ar":"قِوَام"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or subsistence] of the thing is by its"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rukon","text_ar":"رُكْن"},{"kind":"text","text":": not from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlqiyaAm","text_ar":"القِيَام"},{"kind":"text","text":": else it would necessarily be the case that the agent would be a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rukon","text_ar":"رُكْن"},{"kind":"text","text":"to the action; and the substance, to the accident; and the thing to which a quality is attributed, to the quality: (KT:) it is (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that without which the thing has no subsistence:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kull:) and is [also] applied to (assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an essential,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"essential part, of the thing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a part of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maAhiy~ap","text_ar":"مَاهِيَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"essence"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kull, [and in like manner"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arokaAnu Al$~aYo'i","text_ar":"اَرْكَانُ الشَّىْءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is explained in the Msb as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the parts of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mAhy~p","text_ar":"ماهيّة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]) as when we say that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlqiyaAm","text_ar":"القِيَام"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rukon","text_ar":"رُكْن"},{"kind":"text","text":"of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~alaAop","text_ar":"الصَّلَاْة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; as well as to (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the whole"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maAhy~p","text_ar":"مَاهيّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Kull:) [thus]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arokaAnu AlEibaAdaAti","text_ar":"اَرْكَانُ العِبَادَاتِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the fundamentals"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"essentials"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the services of religion, by the neglect,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"non-observance, of which they are ineffectual,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"null,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"void:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or, as some say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rukonu Al$~aYo'i","text_ar":"رُكْنُ الشَّىْءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that whereby the thing is complete;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and this is intrinsic therein; differing from the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aroT","text_ar":"شَرْط"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or condition] thereof, which is extrinsic thereto. (KT.)"}],"source_refs":["Msb","S","K","TA","AHeyth","KT","Kull"]}]}}